toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Nov 14, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104xui1665702780196.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xui1665702780196.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xui1665702780196.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"xui1665702780196\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">You can edit object properties using the Properties Inspector.</p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"xui1665702780196__topic_d4103e1_d4104e1_d4105e1\">It is also possible to edit\n         properties in-line if they are visible in the central editor of a worksheet. For more\n         information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zum1665702619077.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zum1665702619077.html\" title=\"You can rename an object in-line in the Structure Editor, or in the Properties Inspector.\">Rename a Development Object</a>.<p class=\"p\" id=\"xui1665702780196__p_d4109e1_d4110e1_d4111e1\">You\n            can edit the properties of a single object at a time, or set a property on multiple\n            objects to the same value. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wvb1665702780266.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wvb1665702780266.html\" title=\"Use the Property Inspector to set a property on multiple subobjects to the same value. This can be useful, for example, if you want to have several fields use the same data type or same widget type.\">Edit the Properties of Multiple Objects</a>.</p></section>\n<section class=\"section ul\" id=\"xui1665702780196__section_w8960ab1b5b3_w8961ab1b5_w8962ab1\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xui1665702780196__li_d1610e1_d1611e1_d1612e1\">In the worksheet editor, select the object (or\n               objects) you want to edit. The Properties Inspector will display the selected\n               objects' properties.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xui1665702780196__li_d1613e1_d1614e1_d1615e1\">To edit most properties, you can click the property\n               value in the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Object</span> tab of the Properties Inspector, then\n               enter or choose a value. <div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"xui1665702780196__note_w8963ab1b5b3b1b3b3_w8964ab1b5b3b1b3_w8965ab1b5b3b1_w8966ab1b5b3_w8967ab1b5_w8968ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Some properties may have fixed or\n                  inherited values that cannot be changed.</div></li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xui1665702780196__li_d1616e1_d1617e1_d1618e1\">If the property shows the More icon (<img alt=\"The More icon opens a properties dialog.\" class=\"image\" id=\"xui1665702780196__image_rnz_hhf_jzb\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/ellipsis.png?_LANG=enus\"/>) when you move the cursor over it, you can click the icon to open a dialog.\n                  <p class=\"p\" id=\"xui1665702780196__p_d4112e1_d4113e1_d4114e1\">Depending on the property, the dialog enables\n                  you to:</p><ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xui1665702780196__li_d1619e1_d1620e1_d1621e1\">Set a string of property-value pairs. <p class=\"p\" id=\"xui1665702780196__p_d4115e1_d4116e1_d4117e1\">For example, the\n                           <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">ValRep</span> property of fields:</p><figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"xui1665702780196__fig_frg_lhf_jzb\">\n<img alt=\"ValRep Properties dialog of a field\" class=\"image\" id=\"xui1665702780196__image_grg_lhf_jzb\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/pi_valreppropertiesfld_d1b7b58299d48cc151e5923224d4508a.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure></li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xui1665702780196__li_d1622e1_d1623e1_d1624e1\">Define a complex property. <p class=\"p\" id=\"xui1665702780196__p_d4121e1_d4122e1_d4123e1\">For example, the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Database\n                           Interface</span>, <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Field Syntax</span>, and\n                           <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Field Layout</span> properties of fields.</p><figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"xui1665702780196__fig_p4q_mhf_jzb\">\n<img alt=\"Define Field Layout dialog\" class=\"image\" id=\"xui1665702780196__image_q4q_mhf_jzb\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/definefieldlayoutdialog.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure></li>\n</ul><p class=\"p\" id=\"xui1665702780196__p_d4127e1_d4128e1_d4129e1\">Widget properties control the way data is\n                  displayed and edited in the user interface. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uef1704698451038.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uef1704698451038.html\" title=\"Each object that can be viewed in the user interface has a collection of properties that can be used to control what it looks like, and some other aspects of its visual behavior.\">Properties for Styling the User Interface</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xui1665702780196__p_d4130e1_d4131e1_d4132e1\">Consult the widget documentation for the valid\n                  properties and their literal property names. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qxh1718771608803.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qxh1718771608803.html\" title=\"Widgets in dynamic server pages (DSPs) determine the appearance and behavior of fields, labels, occurrences, and entities displayed in the client browser.\">Widget Reference: Dynamic Server Pages</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xcx1665703126648.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xcx1665703126648.html\" title=\"Uniface provides a set of HTML controls for use in static server pages (USPs).\">Widget Reference: Static Server Pages</a>, and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lov1718340866615.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lov1718340866615.html\" title=\"Widgets in Form components determine the appearance and behavior of fields, labels, occurrences, and entities in components running on Windows.\">Widget Reference: Forms and Reports</a>.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xui1665702780196__li_d1625e1_d1626e1_d1627e1\">To edit the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Documentation</span>\n               property, use <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Doc</span> tab. You can enter text of any length and\n               format it using the functionality provided by the toolbar.</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ksl1665702915298.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Development Object Properties</a><p>Every development object has properties which can be viewed and edited in the Properties Inspector.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wvb1665702780266.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Edit the Properties of Multiple Objects</a><p>Use the Property Inspector to set a property on multiple subobjects to the same value. This can be useful, for example, if you want to have several fields use the same data type or same widget type.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533924\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533924\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Edit Object Properties Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Nov 14, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 You can edit object properties using the Properties Inspector. It is also possible to edit properties in-line if they are visible in the central editor of a worksheet. For more information, see Rename a Development Object . You can edit the properties of a single object at a time, or set a property on multiple objects to the same value. For more information, see Edit the Properties of Multiple Objects . In the worksheet editor, select the object (or objects) you want to edit. The Properties Inspector will display the selected objects' properties. To edit most properties, you can click the property value in the Object tab of the Properties Inspector, then enter or choose a value. Note: Some properties may have fixed or inherited values that cannot be changed. If the property shows the More icon ( ) when you move the cursor over it, you can click the icon to open a dialog. Depending on the property, the dialog enables you to: Set a string of property-value pairs. For example, the ValRep property of fields: Define a complex property. For example, the Database Interface , Field Syntax , and Field Layout properties of fields. Widget properties control the way data is displayed and edited in the user interface. For more information, see Properties for Styling the User Interface . Consult the widget documentation for the valid properties and their literal property names. For more information, see Widget Reference: Dynamic Server Pages , Widget Reference: Static Server Pages , and Widget Reference: Forms and Reports . To edit the Documentation property, use Doc tab. You can enter text of any length and format it using the functionality provided by the toolbar. Related Links Development Object Properties Every development object has properties which can be viewed and edited in the Properties Inspector. Edit the Properties of Multiple Objects Use the Property Inspector to set a property on multiple subobjects to the same value. This can be useful, for example, if you want to have several fields use the same data type or same widget type. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}